article.headline: American U. 62, St. Francis, Pa. 52
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Vlad Moldoveanu scored 24 points and American University pulled away to a 62-52 victory over St. Francis (Pa.) in both teams' season opener Friday night. Troy Brewer scored 12 points and Daniel Munoz added 10 for the Eagles, who went 1-6 in out-of-conference home games last season. Mislav Jukic led the Red Flash with 21 points in his first game since Feb. 28, 2009. The senior received a medical redshirt last season after undergoing double hip surgery. Trailing 36-27 at halftime, American took a 42-40 lead on Moldoveanu's putback with 11:06 remaining. His 3-pointer on the previous possession gave the Eagles their first tie of the game. Brewer stretched the lead to four with two free throws. Moldoveanu and Munoz later hit 3-pointers on consecutive possessions to stretch the lead to 52-46 before Munoz connected again on a jumper to push the margin to 10.
